reviewText: I absolutely Loved this play.. Morris Chestnut is such a good looking Black man and the cast was simply beautiful. There was some good singing in this play!!! Avant and Trenyce should have "sang more" but still great. The story line is one all women can identify with and Love the ending!!! Must add this to your collection.
Title: David E. Talbert's Love in the Nick of Tyme

reviewText: It is a very good play, strong actors and a lot of talent. All that and then Mr. Morris Chestnut who is the whipped cream topping. Very nicely done.

Title: David E. Talbert's Love in the Nick of Tyme

reviewText: I have and will always be a fan of Morris Chestnut. From his first movie Boyz N Tha Hood he has captured me and to this day anything he is in I will support. This was good and I always love plays. I recommend this to anyone who needs to let go and move on. Love comes when you least expect it and not looking but like God always on time.
Title: David E. Talbert's Love in the Nick of Tyme
